solution: ```class Solution {
    public int longestSubsequence(String s, int k) {
        int n = s.length();
        int zeros = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) if (c == '0') zeros++;

        long val = 0;
        int len = 0;
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '0') {
                len++;
            } else {
                if (len < 30 && (val | (1L << len)) <= k) {
                    val |= 1L << len;
                    len++;
                }
            }
        }
        return Math.max(len, zeros);
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
